Heat the oil in a medium saucepan and saut√© the pepper slices for 3-4 minutes, to soften. Stir in the tomatoes and heat for a further few minutes.Add the chicken stock, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer gently for 8-10 minutes.Stir in the basil and season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Transfer to a serving bowl and drizzle with a little olive oil, to serve.